#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/introduction/general_tools.rst:168
msgid ""
"Layers in the legend window can be organized into groups. There are two "
"ways to do this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/introduction/general_tools.rst:171
msgid ""
"Press the |folder| icon to add a new group. Type in a name for the group "
"and press :kbd:`Enter`. Now click on an existing layer and drag it onto "
"the group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/introduction/general_tools.rst:174
msgid ""
"Select some layers, right click in the legend window and choose "
":guilabel:`Group Selected`. The selected layers will automatically be "
"placed in a new group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/introduction/general_tools.rst:178
msgid ""
"To bring a layer out of a group, you can drag it out, or right click on "
"it and choose :guilabel:`Move to top-level`; the layer is placed at the "
"same level than the group it was inside. Groups can also be nested inside"
" other groups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/introduction/general_tools.rst:182
msgid ""
"The checkbox for a group will show or hide all the layers in the group "
"with one click."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/introduction/general_tools.rst:185
msgid ""
"Enabling the **Mutually Exclusive Group** option you can make a group "
"have only one layer visible at the same time. Whenever a layer within the"
" group is set visible the others will be toggled not visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/introduction/general_tools.rst:189
msgid ""
"It is possible to select more than one layer or group at the same time by"
" holding down the :kbd:`Ctrl` key while selecting the layers with the "
"left mouse button. You can then move all selected layers to a new group "
"at the same time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/introduction/general_tools.rst:193
msgid ""
"You may also delete more than one layer or group at once by selecting "
"several items with the :kbd:`Ctrl` key and pressing :kbd:`Ctrl+D` "
"afterwards. This way, all selected layers or groups will be removed from "
"the layers list."
msgstr ""

